extracted_text: (6) Impervious coverage. Main and accessory buildings and other impervious cover shall not cover more than 45 percent of lot area on interior lots, and 50 percent of the lot area on corner lots. Accessory buildings shall not cover more than ten percent of the impervious cover requirements.
llm_outputs.rationale: The section titled 'Impervious coverage' under the area regulations for the R-1 Single-Family Dwelling District provides the maximum lot coverage, which is synonymous with 'max_lot_coverage'.
llm_outputs.answer: 45% of lot area on interior lots; 50% of the lot area on corner lots
